
[1]allocation

   ALLOCA'TION, n. [L. ad and locatio, a placing, from locus, place. See
   Local.]

   The act of putting one thing to another; hence its usual sense is the
   admission of an article of account, or an allowance made upon an
   account; a term used in the English Exchequer. [See Allow.]
